          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and study and is a treatise on Hindu philosophy whose title is translated as Bliss of the brahman, title of its second section translated as the Bliss of the self; written from the perspective of the Advaita (non-dualism) Vedānta school of philosophy; work contains part of an extensive commentary called the Tātparyabodhinī by Rāmakṛṣṇa running parallel, above and below, the main root text.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
